-HM, HOW MUCH OLDER?

18:19.228 --> 18:20.795
-OLDER. YOUR AGE.

18:20.925 --> 18:22.101
-UGH. ANTIQUE, HUH?

18:22.231 --> 18:25.321
-NO, I DON'T
MEAN THAT, IT'S JUST...

18:25.974 --> 18:28.368
WELL I'VE NEVER FELT THIS
WAY BEFORE AND I'M AFRAID.

18:29.108 --> 18:30.587
-SOUNDS TO ME LIKE YOU'RE
FALLING IN LOVE, KIDDO.

18:32.241 --> 18:33.982
THAT'S EXACTLY HOW
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO FEEL.

18:34.113 --> 18:35.201
-NO, IT'S...

18:35.940 --> 18:37.551
I JUST DON'T WANT
TO LOSE IT, MITCH.

18:38.117 --> 18:39.161
-WELL IF YOU DON'T
TAKE THE RISK,

18:39.292 --> 18:40.554
YOU WON'T HAVE IT TO LOSE.

18:42.077 --> 18:44.210
-YEAH, I GUESS SO. THANKS.

18:44.340 --> 18:45.124
-ON THE HOUSE.

18:45.254 --> 18:46.995
UH, GOT TO GO.

18:47.648 --> 18:48.866
IT ALWAYS LIFTS YOUR SPIRITS

18:48.997 --> 18:50.390
TALKING TO SOMEONE
WHO'S IN LOVE.

18:51.042 --> 18:52.392
SHE WOULDN'T
REVEAL HER SECRET,

18:52.522 --> 18:54.611
BUT I HAD A CLUE
AS TO WHO IT WAS.

19:12.934 --> 19:13.848
-HEY!

19:13.978 --> 19:15.371
-HEY, WHAT ARE YOU UP TO?

19:15.502 --> 19:17.199
-AH, JUST A LITTLE
SOUL-SEARCHING.

19:17.808 --> 19:19.462
HOW COME YOU DIDN'T MAKE
THE POKER GAME LAST NIGHT?

19:20.507 --> 19:22.987
-I WAS BUSY.
-REALLY?

19:23.597 --> 19:24.772
I HOPE SHE WAS WORTH IT,

19:24.902 --> 19:25.860
I REALLY MISSED
TAKING YOUR MONEY.

19:27.078 --> 19:28.254
-OH, MAYBE YOU'LL
GET IT NEXT WEEK.

19:28.384 --> 19:29.385
AND MAYBE SHE WAS WORTH IT.

19:30.169 --> 19:31.039
-WHAT'S HER NAME?

19:31.170 --> 19:32.562
-EH, IT DOESN'T MATTER.

19:32.693 --> 19:34.085
YOU KNOW IT'S PROBABLY
NOT GONNA WORK OUT

19:34.216 --> 19:35.913
AND TRUTH IS IT SCARES
ME HALF TO DEATH.

19:36.044 --> 19:38.481
-EVEN A SEASONED VETERAN
LIKE CRAIG POMEROY.

19:39.265 --> 19:40.831
-AFTER MY DIVORCE FROM GINA,

19:42.572 --> 19:44.444
WELL HEARTS GET BROKEN.

19:44.574 --> 19:46.141
I DON'T THINK I EVER WANT
TO GO THROUGH THAT AGAIN.

19:47.621 --> 19:49.797
-AFTER GAYLE AND
I GOT DIVORCED,

19:49.927 --> 19:51.320
THE THOUGHT OF
GETTING INVOLVED

19:51.451 --> 19:52.974
WITH ANOTHER WOMAN WAS
OUT OF THE QUESTION.

19:53.496 --> 19:54.367
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT?

19:54.497 --> 19:55.368
IT GOES AWAY, BUDDY.

19:55.498 --> 19:57.108
SO GO FOR IT, GIVE IT A TRY.

19:57.239 --> 19:58.501
-NAH, IT'S TOO SOON.

19:58.632 --> 19:59.894
TOO RISKY, I MEAN WHAT IF?

20:00.024 --> 20:01.156
-WHAT IF, WHAT IF?

20:01.287 --> 20:02.592
THERE'S ALWAYS A IF.

20:02.723 --> 20:03.941
IT'S CALLED LIFE.

20:04.464 --> 20:05.682
I MEAN FOR GOD'S SAKES,

20:06.248 --> 20:08.685
THERE'S AN "IF" RIGHT IN THE
MIDDLE OF THE WORD LIFE.

20:11.645 --> 20:14.038
-THAT'S INCREDIBLY CORNY
AND I'VE HEARD IT BEFORE.

20:14.169 --> 20:15.953
-NOT THAT PART ABOUT "IF" IN
THE MIDDLE OF THE WORD LIFE,

20:16.084 --> 20:17.128
'CAUSE I-- I JUST
MADE THAT UP.

20:17.259 --> 20:18.826
-WELL THEN THAT'S PRETTY GOOD.

20:18.956 --> 20:19.740
-THANK YOU, I THOUGHT SO.

20:19.870 --> 20:20.697
-YOU'RE WELCOME.

20:20.828 --> 20:22.003
[ENGINE REVVING]

20:22.786 --> 20:24.092
-LOOK AT THAT BOAT.

20:24.223 --> 20:27.313
[WOMAN SCREAMING]

20:28.836 --> 20:29.880
-COME ON, LET'S GO!

20:40.848 --> 20:41.892
LOOK LIKE THE
THROTTLE'S JAMMED.

20:42.023 --> 20:43.416
COME ON, LET'S GO!

21:29.766 --> 21:31.028
-APRIL: IT'S
OKAY, HANG IN THERE.

21:31.159 --> 21:32.595
-MITCH: GET AS
CLOSE AS YOU CAN.

21:33.640 --> 21:35.946
OKAY, ALL RIGHT. AH!

21:53.050 --> 21:54.878
ALL RIGHT, THERE YOU GO.

21:58.360 --> 21:59.927
YOU ALL RIGHT?
-YEAH.

22:00.057 --> 22:02.364
ALL RIGHT. PUT THIS
AROUND YOU, STAY WARM.

22:03.713 --> 22:05.149
-APRIL: HEY, CAN I BUM A RIDE?

22:07.587 --> 22:10.677
-NEXT TIME, DON'T FORGET
TO WEAR YOUR LEASH, HUH?

22:10.807 --> 22:12.069
THIS KILLS THE
ENGINE, ALL RIGHT?

22:12.200 --> 22:13.027
-OKAY.

22:13.157 --> 22:14.028
-CRAIG: HEY LAST NIGHT?

22:14.158 --> 22:16.639
-I LOVED IT.
-ME, TOO.

22:17.205 --> 22:19.250
-WELL, WELL, WELL.

22:19.381 --> 22:23.167
IF I WERE YOU TWO, I'D
DEFINITELY TAKE THE RISK.

22:30.000 --> 22:31.088
WELL WHAT A SURPRISE.

22:31.611 --> 22:33.177
HEY, IF IT WORKS FOR
THEM IT WORKS FOR ME.

22:33.308 --> 22:34.875
AS LONG AS IT
MAKES YOU HAPPY.

22:36.616 --> 22:37.617
HEY!

22:38.182 --> 22:39.880
-HEY, MITCH, WHAT ARE
YOU DOING OUT THERE?

22:40.010 --> 22:41.272
I BEEN WATCHING YOU FOR HOURS.

22:41.403 --> 22:42.186
-AH, JUST WORKING
SOME THINGS OUT.

22:43.362 --> 22:44.972
LISTEN, YOU NEED TO FILL
OUT AN INCIDENT REPORT

22:45.102 --> 22:45.886
ON THAT RESCUE YOU MADE.

22:46.016 --> 22:47.278
-YEAH, SURE, NO BIG DEAL.

22:47.409 --> 22:49.106
-YOU WANT TO FILL ME IN?

22:49.237 --> 22:51.282
-SURE. WE DIDN'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT WE WERE LOOKING AT

22:51.413 --> 22:52.893
UNTIL WE GOT DOWN THERE.

23:05.253 --> 23:07.647
CODY KNEW THE LITTLE
GIRLS WERE TOP PRIORITY,

23:07.777 --> 23:09.388
SO HE GOT ME TO SWIM 'EM UP,

23:09.518 --> 23:11.651
YOU KNOW, ABOUT A SECOND
BEFORE THEY WERE GONERS.

23:13.479 --> 23:16.438
THEY WERE SAFE SO I WENT
BACK DOWN TO HELP CODY OUT.

23:16.569 --> 23:18.092
CODY WAS ON TOP OF THINGS.

23:18.222 --> 23:20.790
THOSE UNIFORMS THE COPS
HAD ON WERE WATERLOGGED.

23:21.487 --> 23:23.489
I MEAN, THEY WERE DROWNING.

23:23.619 --> 23:25.273
I STARTED HELPING HIM
YANK THEIR CLOTHES OFF.

23:25.404 --> 23:27.144
I JUST FOLLOWED HIS LEAD.

23:27.275 --> 23:29.277
THEN WE GOT 'EM
UP, SIMPLE REALLY.

23:29.408 --> 23:30.757
-DIDN'T SOUND SIMPLE TO ME.

23:31.322 --> 23:32.628
SOUNDS LIKE A TERRIFIC RESCUE.

23:32.759 --> 23:34.108
-YEAH?
-YEAH.

23:34.238 --> 23:35.718
-WELL, IT WAS MOSTLY CODY.

23:36.240 --> 23:39.026
I JUST DID WHAT I GET
PAID TO DO, SAVE LIVES.

23:39.156 --> 23:41.158
-DO ME A FAVOR, CHECK
WITH ME AFTER YOUR SHIFT

23:41.289 --> 23:42.333
AND, UH, SIGN THE REPORT, HUH?

23:42.464 --> 23:43.422
-OKAY.

23:44.640 --> 23:45.989
LIKE I SAID, IT
WAS MOSTLY CODY.

23:46.120 --> 23:46.990
-YEAH.

23:47.121 --> 23:48.035
-PIECE OF CAKE FOR ME.

23:48.165 --> 23:49.123
-SEE YA.

23:53.170 --> 23:54.737
-YOU KNOW, SWEETHEART,

23:54.868 --> 23:56.347
THE HIGH FALL IS ONE OF
THE MOVIES' CLASSIC STUNTS.

23:56.957 --> 23:58.219
-ARE YOU SURE YOU
KNOW WHAT YOU'RE DOING?

23:58.349 --> 23:59.873
-OH, I'M A PRO, LAMB CHOP.

24:00.003 --> 24:01.875
LISTEN, A STUNT MAN
LEAVES NOTHING TO CHANCE.

24:02.005 --> 24:03.659
THIS IS AN ART FORM
AND I'M AN ARTIST.

24:03.790 --> 24:05.705
YOU STICK BY MY SIDE AND
YOU'LL LEARN SOMETHING.

24:05.835 --> 24:07.707
-OKAY.

24:07.837 --> 24:09.230
-SEE THAT MATTRESS IS DOWN
THERE TO BREAK YOUR FALL,

24:09.360 --> 24:11.014
BUT THERE'S A FEW THINGS
YOU GOT TO COMPUTE:

24:11.145 --> 24:12.625
YOUR HEIGHT, YOUR WEIGHT,

24:12.755 --> 24:14.844
THE ANGLE OF DESCENT, THE
GRAVITY CONFIGURATION.

24:14.975 --> 24:16.237
ARE YOU TAKING
NOTES, BY THE WAY?

24:16.367 --> 24:17.499
-NO, BUT I'M WITH YOU.

24:17.630 --> 24:19.240
-AND, OF COURSE,
WE CAN'T FORGET

24:19.936 --> 24:21.590
THE PREVAILING
WINDS THIS TIME.

24:21.721 --> 24:24.288
-UH, YOU KNOW, I REALLY DON'T
THINK YOU SHOULD DO THIS.

24:24.419 --> 24:26.726
-COME ON, THIS IS
BASIC STUNTS 101.

24:26.856 --> 24:28.118
LOOK, I TELL YOU WHAT.

24:28.249 --> 24:29.729
LET'S SAY YOU'RE
THE CAMERA, OKAY?

24:29.859 --> 24:31.600
AND WE'RE AT THE TOP OF
THE EMPIRE STATE BUILDING

24:31.731 --> 24:34.821
AND TOM CRUISE IS-- IS BEING
CHASED BY SOME BAD GUY,

24:34.951 --> 24:36.213
AND HE'S GOT A KNIFE.

24:36.344 --> 24:37.301
AND TOM CRUISE DOESN'T
KNOW WHAT TO DO,

24:37.432 --> 24:38.564
AND THE MUSIC COMES UP,

24:38.694 --> 24:40.479
DUM, DUM, DUM,
DUM, DUM, DUM.

24:40.609 --> 24:42.176
AND ALL OF A SUDDEN,
FOR NO REASON,

24:42.306 --> 24:44.526
HE JUST JUMPS UP LIKE
THIS ON THE RAILING, OKAY?

24:45.048 --> 24:46.572
ALL RIGHT, AND
THEN WHAT HAPPENS?

24:46.702 --> 24:49.662
CUT. AND WEENIE, WIMPY
ACTOR TOM CRUISE STEPS DOWN

24:49.792 --> 24:52.229
AND STUNT MAN
EXTRAORDINAIRE, ED SYMES,

24:52.360 --> 24:53.448
STEPS IN TO DOUBLE HIM.

24:55.755 --> 24:57.191
OKAY, NOW GO AHEAD
AND SHOOT ME.

24:57.321 --> 24:59.193
-UM, YOU KNOW, I
REALLY DON'T THINK

24:59.323 --> 25:00.107
THIS IS SUCH A GOOD IDEA.

25:00.237 --> 25:01.369
-OH, IT'S A GREAT IDEA.

25:01.500 --> 25:02.588
COME ON NOW, SHOOT ME.

25:02.718 --> 25:05.504
COME ON, JUST
SHOOT ME. SHOOT ME!

25:07.288 --> 25:08.811
-BANG.
-OOH!

25:17.428 --> 25:19.692
-AH!
-ED: UH-OH.

25:23.304 --> 25:24.784
-OH MY GOSH, ARE YOU OKAY?

25:41.061 --> 25:42.932
HEY, ARE YOU OKAY?

25:43.063 --> 25:47.371
-OH, YEAH.
ABSOLUTELY, ABSOLUTELY.

25:47.502 --> 25:49.678
-ED, DON'T TAKE
THIS PERSONALLY?

25:49.809 --> 25:51.419
-OKAY.
-BUT YOU'RE FIRED.

25:51.550 --> 25:53.726
-WHAT? WHY WOULD YOU FIRE ME?

25:53.856 --> 25:55.336
-TO SAVE YOUR LIFE.

25:55.466 --> 25:56.555
-WELL, WAIT A MINUTE.

25:56.685 --> 25:58.165
WE-- WE COULD DISCUSS THIS.

25:58.295 --> 25:59.470
I MEAN, AFTER ALL, I JUST...

25:59.601 --> 26:02.735
HEY, OH, OH.

26:02.865 --> 26:04.563
I THINK I'LL LIE DOWN
FOR JUST A LITTLE WHILE.

26:11.091 --> 26:12.788
-MITCH: MY NEXT
STOP WAS CODY'S TOWER

26:12.919 --> 26:15.486
SO I COULD GET HIS VERSION
OF THE PIER RESCUE.

26:15.617 --> 26:17.576
THERE'S SOMETHING
ABOUT J.D.'S VERSION

26:17.706 --> 26:19.360
THAT DIDN'T SEEM QUITE RIGHT.

26:22.581 --> 26:25.192
-CODY: HEY! DOING
THE TOWER SWIM, HUH?

26:25.845 --> 26:26.889
-I TALKED TO J.D.

26:27.411 --> 26:29.196
A PRETTY HAIRY
PIER RESCUE, HUH?

26:29.326 --> 26:30.893
-NAH, PIECE OF CAKE.

26:31.590 --> 26:32.634
-REALLY?

26:32.765 --> 26:33.896
-YEAH.
-THAT'S WHAT HE SAID.

26:34.027 --> 26:35.637
-I JUST DID WHAT
HE TOLD ME TO DO.

26:35.768 --> 26:37.726
-WELL HE TOLD ME HE
FOLLOWED YOUR LEAD

26:37.857 --> 26:39.032
AND THAT YOU TOOK CHARGE.

26:39.162 --> 26:42.252
-NO. HE KNEW WHAT
TO DO RIGHT AWAY.

26:57.659 --> 27:00.444
FROM THE GET-GO, J.D. SAW THAT
THE COPS WERE IN TROUBLE.

27:00.575 --> 27:02.838
THEIR UNIFORMS WERE
TOTALLY WATERLOGGED, MAN.

27:02.969 --> 27:05.275
THEY PROBABLY WEIGHED
300 POUNDS IN THE WATER.

27:12.456 --> 27:14.589
J.D. KNEW THAT THE LITTLE
GIRLS CAME FIRST.

27:14.720 --> 27:16.112
HE GRABBED THEM
AND THEN SIGNALED

27:16.243 --> 27:17.766
FOR ME TO YANK THE
CLOTHES OFF THE COPS.

27:31.127 --> 27:32.476
-SO YOU'RE TELLING ME THAT J.D.

27:32.607 --> 27:33.956
ASSUMED COMMAND OF
THE RESCUE, NOT YOU?

27:34.087 --> 27:36.480
-YEAH. LISTEN, I'D LOVE
TO BE IN THE SPOTLIGHT,

27:36.611 --> 27:39.396
BUT IT WAS J.D. WHO DID
ALL THE RIGHT STUFF.

27:40.093 --> 27:41.572
-OKAY. DO ME A FAVOR.

27:41.703 --> 27:43.009
FILL OUT AN
INCIDENT REPORT, EH?

27:43.139 --> 27:44.010
-YOU GOT IT.

27:44.793 --> 27:46.490
-ALL RIGHT, SEE YA.
-GO GET 'EM.

28:15.128 --> 28:16.956
-WHY'D YOU TELL MITCH I WAS
SOME KIND OF BIG-TIME HERO?

28:17.086 --> 28:18.131
-WHY'D YOU TELL HIM I WAS?

28:18.261 --> 28:19.872
-'CAUSE YOU WERE THE MAN, J.D..

28:20.394 --> 28:22.352
-HEY, WE BOTH JUST
DID WHAT WE HAD TO DO.

28:22.483 --> 28:23.614
IT'S NO BIGGIE.

28:23.745 --> 28:25.399
-NO, BUT MAYBE
IT WAS, YOU KNOW?

28:25.921 --> 28:27.314
I MEAN, BOTH CRAIG AND APRIL

28:27.444 --> 28:28.532
WANT TO NOMINATE US
FOR THE MEDAL OF VALOR,

28:28.663 --> 28:29.708
GETTING US ALL PUMPED UP?

28:30.578 --> 28:31.448
MAYBE WE EARNED IT.

28:32.232 --> 28:33.624
-NAH, IT'S ALL
PART OF THE JOB.

28:34.147 --> 28:35.322
IT WAS NOTHING SPECIAL.

28:35.452 --> 28:37.150
-AH, MAYBE YOU'RE RIGHT.

28:38.064 --> 28:40.022
MEDALS OF VALOR BELONG
TO THE REAL PROS,

28:40.153 --> 28:42.068
THE MITCHES, THE NEWMIES.

28:42.677 --> 28:44.287
-WE'RE NOT HALF THE
LIFEGUARDS THOSE GUYS ARE.

28:45.071 --> 28:46.202
-SOMEDAY, MAYBE.

28:46.986 --> 28:48.596
-YEAH, SOMEDAY.

28:49.379 --> 28:52.252
-WELL, AT LEAST WE
CAN DREAM, YOU KNOW?

28:52.905 --> 28:55.168
-YUP. AND SOMETIMES
DREAMS COME TRUE.

28:55.995 --> 28:59.215
GOT TO GO. HEY, YOU
WERE GOOD DOWN THERE.

28:59.955 --> 29:01.478
-YOU, TOO. I'LL SEE YA.

29:09.617 --> 29:11.227
-MITCH: BY THIS TIME,
AS YOU CAN IMAGINE,

29:11.358 --> 29:13.055
I'M GETTING PRETTY TIRED.

29:13.186 --> 29:16.363
BUT STILL, THIS CODY-J.D.
THING DIDN'T MAKE ANY SENSE.

29:17.059 --> 29:19.453
WHY WERE THEY MAKING EACH
OTHER OUT TO BE THE HERO?

29:20.323 --> 29:22.717
THEN I REALIZED I
WASN'T ALONE OUT THERE.

29:23.283 --> 29:26.112
WHAT THE HECK WAS A DOG DOING
THAT FAR OFF FROM SHORE?

29:26.242 --> 29:29.376
WELL, A RESCUE IS A RESCUE,
AND I AM A LIFEGUARD.

29:29.506 --> 29:31.682
SO, I CAME TO HIS AID.

29:43.303 --> 29:44.826
HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY BUDDY.

29:44.957 --> 29:46.785
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
SO FAR OUT HERE, HUH?

29:46.915 --> 29:48.525
[DOG WHINING]
HUH?

29:49.222 --> 29:51.485
YOU'RE REALLY FAR OFF
SHORE, ARE YOU OKAY?

29:51.615 --> 29:54.923
YOU JUST TAKE IT EASY BECAUSE
I AM AN LA COUNTY LIFEGUARD,

29:55.054 --> 29:56.403
AND I'M GOING
TO SAVE YOU, OKAY?

29:56.533 --> 29:57.534
LET'S GO.

29:57.665 --> 29:59.058
HEY, THAT A BOY.

29:59.188 --> 29:59.972
LET'S GO.

30:00.102 --> 30:01.669
YEAH, THAT A BOY.

30:02.713 --> 30:04.193
YEAH, THAT A BOY.

30:07.327 --> 30:10.025
AND JUST LIKE THAT I
HAD A NEW BEST FRIEND.

30:10.156 --> 30:11.984
YEAH, YOU'RE ALL RIGHT, PAL.

30:12.114 --> 30:13.420
LET'S GET YOU DRIED OFF HERE,

30:13.550 --> 30:15.204
YOU'LL BE AS GOOD AS NEW.

30:18.381 --> 30:19.905
3HEY, HOW'S YOUR
STUNT INSTRUCTOR?

30:20.427 --> 30:23.125
-UGH, YOU DON'T WANT TO BE
AN I TOLD YOU SO, DO YOU?

30:23.256 --> 30:25.388
-NOPE, BUT
I TOLD YOU SO.

30:27.390 --> 30:29.001
-HEY, WHO YOU GOT HERE?

30:29.131 --> 30:31.220
-I DON'T KNOW, HE
DOESN'T HAVE A COLLAR.

30:31.351 --> 30:33.744
I FOUND HIM TREADING
WATER JUST OFFSHORE.

30:33.875 --> 30:35.137
-DID HE JUST SWIM OUT THERE?

30:35.268 --> 30:38.314
-MAYBE. MAYBE HE
FELL OFF A BOAT OR...

30:38.445 --> 30:40.534
MAYBE SOME MORON
THREW HIM OVERBOARD.

30:41.230 --> 30:43.493
ANYWAY HE'S NAMELESS
AND HOMELESS.

30:43.624 --> 30:46.018
-AW.
[DOG WHIMPERING]

30:49.325 --> 30:50.979
-UH, DO ME A FAVOR, WOULD YOU,

30:51.110 --> 30:52.415
AND WATCH HIM FOR
A COUPLE MINUTES?

30:52.546 --> 30:54.156
-YEAH, SURE. HAPPY TO.

30:55.462 --> 30:57.943
BABY, I'M GOING TO
LOVE ON YOU, OKAY?

31:09.128 --> 31:10.259
-WHAT?

31:10.390 --> 31:12.261
-YOU LOOK LIKE
BOB'S BIG BOY.

31:12.392 --> 31:13.959
WHAT HAPPENED,
CHIPMUNK DIE?

31:15.003 --> 31:16.787
-I WALKED PAST HER
THREE TIMES ON PURPOSE.

31:16.918 --> 31:18.354
SHE DIDN'T EVEN NOTICE ME.

31:18.485 --> 31:19.747
-THIS, YOU NOTICE.

31:19.878 --> 31:21.227
WHY DON'T YOU
JUST BE YOURSELF?

31:21.357 --> 31:22.402
-I HAVE BEEN.

31:23.272 --> 31:24.926
NOT SO MUCH AS A SMILE.

31:25.666 --> 31:28.060
-NEWMIE, YOU'RE TRYING TO
BE SOMEONE THAT YOU'RE NOT.

31:28.190 --> 31:31.411
-YEAH? WELL JUST
WHO AM I ANYWAY, HUH?

31:31.541 --> 31:34.457
I'M JUST SOME LIFEGUARD GETTING
OLD AND BALD ON THE BEACH.

31:34.588 --> 31:36.895
I DON'T KNOW, I'M THINKING
ABOUT GOING BACK TO SCHOOL.

31:38.026 --> 31:40.637
GETTING A REAL JOB,
BECOMING SOMEBODY IMPORTANT.

31:41.638 --> 31:44.380
-I FELT THE SAME WAY,
EXCEPT FOR THE BALD PART.

31:45.120 --> 31:47.818
I WONDERED IF I WAS SOMEONE
WHO REALLY MATTERED.

31:47.949 --> 31:49.908
SOMEONE WHO DID
SOMETHING WITH HIS LIFE.

31:50.038 --> 31:52.301
OR DID I WANNA WAKE
UP ONE DAY, AN OLD MAN

31:52.432 --> 31:55.174
IN RED SHORTS, ASKING
MYSELF THIS QUESTION:

31:56.175 --> 31:58.220
MITCH BUCHANNON, ARE
YOU AN IMPORTANT PERSON?

31:58.351 --> 31:59.961
DID YOU MAKE A CONTRIBUTION?

32:00.788 --> 32:01.658
BIG QUESTION.

32:02.703 --> 32:04.226
-WHAT WAS THE ANSWER?

32:04.357 --> 32:05.793
-HELL YES.

32:05.924 --> 32:07.664
I WORK WITH PEOPLE
WHO NEED ME.

32:07.795 --> 32:09.144
I SAVE LIVES.

32:09.797 --> 32:11.973
I COULD TAKE ANOTHER JOB
AND MAKE A MILLION DOLLARS,

32:12.104 --> 32:14.497
BUT NO AMOUNT OF MONEY CAN
GIVE YOU THE FEELING YOU GET

32:14.628 --> 32:16.412
WHEN YOU SAVE SOMEONE'S LIFE.

32:16.543 --> 32:17.979
YOU KNOW THAT FEELING, NEWMIE.

32:18.937 --> 32:19.850
-I DO.

32:21.200 --> 32:22.853
HM, AND I LIKE IT.

